Traumatic instability of the sternoclavicular joint is a rare diagnosis. It is usually treated by different bandaging techniques without the possibility of early functional aftercare. In the period betweeen 1 January 1996 and 31 December 1998, a total of eight patients with unstable sternoclavicular joints requiring surgical treatment were treated with Balser plates. The population comprised sevenanterior and one posterior dislocations.  
